properties.Title: Arlington, VA - Yang Hang at Feel the Heritage Festival
properties.Description:
Join the Northern Virginia Yang as we promote Andrew yang at this amazing festival, everyone is welcome as we celebrate Arlington’s rich African-American history at the 28th annual Feel the Heritage Festival on Sat., Feb. 29, 1-6 p.m., Drew Community Center. This FREE Black History Month event will feature live music and dance, dozens of vendors, free activities for kids, delicious food, cook-off competition, Hall of History with photos and artifacts for Arlington’s historically African-American neighborhoods and organizations and more.

Artisan vendors will be selling everything to homemade soaps, candles and hot sauces to apparel, jewelry, hair bows, handbags and much more. Community groups will have information about their programs and services and lots of fun giveaways.
Free activities will include:

- Craft projects
- Giant games – Checkers, chess, Chinese checkers
- Face painting
- Balloon art
- Event Passport – pick up a passport at the event information table, answer all of the questions and get a prize,
- ... lots more!

Details: https://parks.arlingtonva.us/feel-the-heritage-festival/

properties.Title: San Antonio, TX - #HumanityFirst, Downtown Dinners for the homeless
properties.Venue: Parking lot of church under the bridge
properties.Description:
San Antonio Yang Gang come out and serve food to homeless in coordination with Taking It To The Streets.
Taking It To The Streets is a non profit organization they serve dinner in a family-style setting in downtown San Antonio to homeless men, women, and children on Saturday evenings. They have been serving and loving on the impoverished and homeless for 9+ years in San Antonio Texas. To learn more about this wonderful organization please check here. Www.takingittothestreets.com

They serve dinner every Saturday night, rain or shine! On Saturday February 15th, please arrive at 6:15pm at 724 Chestnut St, San Antonio, TX 78202 for volunteer orientation and set-up. They serve dinner at 7pm and have normally wrapped up and cleaned up by 8:30pm.

They serve from 724 Chestnut Street, which is the gated parking lot of Church Under the Bridge.  In inclement weather, we serve inside the church in the fellowship hall.

properties.Title: Seattle, WA - Mitigating Climate Change with Atoms
properties.Venue: University Branch - The Seattle Public Library
properties.Description:
Andrew's policies have something for everyone. And we are a curious group! Local experts on Nuclear energy want to help share their knowledge and excited that Andrew has included this piece in the climate change discussion.

Come have a discussion about the prospects of atomic energy as a tool to help mitigate climate change. The USA generated 4.2 billion megawatt-hours of clean-air, low-carbon electricity by splitting atoms in 2018, making up 19% of the USA's total electricity. Yet, this energy source is controversial and hotly debated. Its low-carbon nature is inspiring many young scientists and engineers to enter the field, and is causing many environmentalists to reconsider their positions on it in the face of the potential consequences of climate change.

We will be featuring a local advanced reactor designer and founder of whatisnuclear.com (Nick Touran, Ph.D. in Nuclear Engineering from the University of Michigan) and an ecopragmatist from the Seattle Ecomodernist Society (Karl Pauls). They will present that history, current status, and future prospects of nuclear technology, including details about Thorium fuel as discussed in the Democratic debates by Andrew Yang. The highlight will be the Q&A discussion session afterwards, so come with questions!

properties.Title: Arcata, CA - Yang Gang Hang
properties.Description:
Thanks for signing up to attend the Humboldt County Yang Gang Hang!

This will be a casual meetup at the Ramones in Wildberries (the sun room) on every Saturday @ 6:30pm to discuss how to get involved with the campaign and plan for the coming weeks. Specifically will be discussing getting things together for phonebanking parties, fundraisers, and the usual tabling and yanging at local events! The cafe isn't the biggest so will be easy to spot. Look for the redhead with the Yanged out laptop!

Connecting through our Facebook group "Humboldt County Yang Gang" is great, but getting supporters together in-real-life (IRL) is how we can really grow and help Andrew win! The purpose of this meeting is just to get to know other Yang supporters in our community, talk about what drew us to the campaign, and discuss ways to get Andrew to the White House - making calls, sending texts, knocking on doors, but also fun actions at local community events!

This is to be a fairly informal meeting. Don’t feel obligated to prepare anything before hand or feel like you need to have prior campaigning experience to show up. We just want to start building a Yang Gang presence in our community as we approach the Democratic Primary beginning with that early voting in February.

This will hopefully be a great place to prepare for canvassing and brainstorm creative ways to make everyone aware of Yang's message. Bring your ideas, and I will bring Yang Cards to share!

And really this location is just to start, but we can change it if someone thinks up or can offer a more suitable place -and the time as well if another works better for everybody. Can't wait to see everyone there!

Below is what we plan to do:
* Immediately send Voter Identification texts to thousands of potential voters

This is a private business that is offering office space for Yang Gang text banking. The max capacity is 12 people at a time. You do not have to stay for the full hours of this event, but the minimum hours of volunteering that's expected is 2.

Feel free to bring a potluck of food and drinks to share. There are also local restaurants on the ground floor of this building.

Drop in at any time between Noon-4pm, whether it's 30 min, an hour, two hours, however much time you can dedicate to get Yang elected!

Just bring your own laptop, earbuds/headphones, and a positive attitude :)

---

January schedule:

- Sat 1/4 @ 425 Market#900, Host: Eric


- Sat 1/11 @ 680 Folsom, Host: Elaine


- Sat 1/18 @ 601 Townsend, Host: Musa (NOTE: Due to SF Women's March, this will be from 4-6pm)

- You won't be using your personal phone number, the Yang Dialer will automatically dial for you

properties.Title: Arcata CA - Tabling @ Arcata's Farmer's Market
properties.Description:
Weekly tabling every Sat. 10am - 2pm at the Arcata Farmer's Market! As name recognition continues to go up and up for Yang, the need also increases to go beyond that and help people connect that name to the policies and Humanity First philosophy that are our reasons for supporting him in the first place!

Help connect interested community members with other Yang supporters, show how they can help too, share with the Yang-curious why you support Yang over the crowd of other candidates, and help spread that correct information over mis-information (make America think harder)!

This is our opportunity to have face-to-face conversations with the community-at-large, grow our grassroots base, and make lasting impressions that are far more impactful and lasting than the mere sharing of talking points!

Email to designate a specific time slot, or just come on down and give moral support on your break -the more the merrier!

Chairs, table, and logistics are all taken care of, but what we are always in need of are more materials (Prints: infographics, cards, posters), let us know what you can contribute by email or call, or/and drop off your favorite material from yangprints.com or elsewhere. And, if you simply want to help but don't know specifically how, simply contact us and we'll move you forward!

Can't wait to see you there, -Humanity First!

Hi Gilbert Yang Gang you're all invited to join us at the Coffee Shop near Joe's Farm Grill to get to know your local Yang Gang and to text bank the early primary States. Specifically will be discussing getting things together for phonebanking parties, fundraisers, and the usual tabling and yanging at local events! The cafe isn't the biggest so will be easy to spot. Look for the redhead with the Yanged out laptop!

Connecting through our Facebook group "Humboldt County Yang Gang" is great, but getting supporters together in-real-life (IRL) is how we can really grow and help Andrew win! The purpose of this meeting is just to get to know other Yang supporters in our community, talk about what drew us to the campaign, and discuss ways to get Andrew to the White House - making calls, sending texts, knocking on doors, but also fun actions at local community events!

This is to be a fairly informal meeting. Don’t feel obligated to prepare anything before hand or feel like you need to have prior campaigning experience to show up. We just want to start building a Yang Gang presence in our community as we approach the Democratic Primary beginning with that early voting in February.

This will hopefully be a great place to prepare for canvassing and brainstorm creative ways to make everyone aware of Yang's message. Bring your ideas, and I will bring Yang Cards to share!

And really this location is just to start, but we can change it if someone thinks up or can offer a more suitable place -and the time as well if another works better for everybody. Can't wait to see everyone there!

The Candidate Fair (the part where Yang Gang volunteers are needed) is from 1 to 3 PM. Volunteers are welcome to attend the entire day, if they would like.

Volunteers will be sitting at a table and approached by students during the two-hour period. Two to three Yang Gang volunteers would be ideal, so please only sign up for this if you can seriously commit. JSA will provide the table; we just bring signs, information materials, handouts and sign-up sheets.

Please note that there is another tabling event on this day at the Grand Lake Farmers Market from 9 to 2 (https://www.mobilize.us/yang2020/event/186598/). It would be great if those who volunteer for the JSA event could pick up the materials from the farmers market table at about noon before proceeding to Jack London Square.

Email to designate a specific time slot, or just come on down and give moral support on your break -the more the merrier!

properties.Title: Rhode Island Signature Gathering - 1st opportunity to sign & to get signatures for Andrew Yang!
properties.Description:
**The nomination papers will be fresh off the presses & this will be our first signature collection opportunity in Rhode Island!**

The Rhode Island process is very fast. From the time we pick up the nomination papers (Thu 1/23) to when the whole process of gathering, notarizing, and submitting 1k+ signatures must be finished (Thu 2/6 by 4pm), we have just two weeks to put Andrew Yang on the RI ballot.

Very do-able, but we just have to be organized. (Every candidate is going thru this same process.)

**Before coming to the event:**

- please review our signature gathering guide: http://bit.ly/RISigGuide
- please listen to this 11 min clip: https://youtu.be/hGyB5eJEGJI

We'll be meeting at the Starbucks in One Financial, doing a quick training, and then walking over to Kennedy Plaza transit center to gather signatures from registered voters waiting for their buses home (and possibly a group will head over to the Providence Place mall too).

PLEASE BRING A CLIPBOARD!

**Afterward**, we're going to walk over to **Sakis Pizzeria (199 Weybosset St)** for a post-collection Yang Gang Hang. Something to eat & an opportunity to plan where everyone is going to gather signatures over the weekend!

Let’s get Andrew Yang on the ballot!

This will be a casual meetup at the Ramones in Wildberries (the sun room) on every Wednesday @ 5:30pm to discuss how to get involved with the campaign and plan for the coming weeks. Specifically will be discussing getting things together for phonebanking parties, fundraisers, and the usual tabling and yanging at local events! The cafe isn't the biggest so will be easy to spot. Look for the redhead with the Yanged out laptop!

Connecting through our Facebook group "Humboldt County Yang Gang" is great, but getting supporters together in-real-life (IRL) is how we can really grow and help Andrew win! The purpose of this meeting is just to get to know other Yang supporters in our community, talk about what drew us to the campaign, and discuss ways to get Andrew to the White House - making calls, sending texts, knocking on doors, but also fun actions at local community events!

This is to be a fairly informal meeting. Don’t feel obligated to prepare anything before hand or feel like you need to have prior campaigning experience to show up. We just want to start building a Yang Gang presence in our community as we approach the Democratic Primary beginning with that early voting in February.

This will hopefully be a great place to prepare for canvassing and brainstorm creative ways to make everyone aware of Yang's message. Bring your ideas, and I will bring Yang Cards to share!

And really this location is just to start, but we can change it if someone thinks up or can offer a more suitable place -and the time as well if another works better for everybody. Can't wait to see everyone there!

Tue 1/21/20 8:00am - 8:00pm EST

Help Andrew Yang and our NY CD-4 delegates get on the ballot! We've been given a tall order - to collect a whole bunch of signatures (5000 for our Presidential candidate, 500 for each delegate!) before early February. Let's crush these goals and keep this campaign rolling. CD-2 and -3 Yangsters may also have a good amount of luck here, so please come out to support us!

This is the first day of classes in the Spring Semester at NCC, so hopefully we'll catch people after syllabus week lectures and not when they're bogged down with work.

Feel free to swing by at any time during the 8AM - 8PM window, but would really appreciate if you could spend at least ~2-3 hours helping out the campaign. We'll be busy collecting signatures for the most part, but I'm planning to have down time so we can bake a Yang Gang Hang into this day! :) Let's meet some local Yang Gang members, Yang some Long Islanders (super important, because we need more than 15% of votes for a Congressional District to secure DNC delegates), and help Make America Think Harder!

properties.Description:
Join us in reading Dr. King's "Where Do We Go From Here: Chaos or Community?"

We will host a discussion about Dr. King's book, including it's role in Andrew Yang's vision for creating universal basic income, on MLK day at Cypress & Grove. All are welcome.

[From Wiki]
Where Do We Go from Here: Chaos or Community? is a 1967 book by African-American minister, Nobel Peace Prize laureate, and social justice campaigner Martin Luther King, Jr. Advocating for human rights and a sense of hope, it was King's fourth and last book before his assassination. He spent a long period in isolation, living in a rented residence in Jamaica with no telephone, composing the book.It later lapsed out of print until Beacon Press published an expanded edition in 2010, which featured a new introduction passage by King's long-time friend Vincent Gordon Harding and a foreword by King's wife, Coretta Scott King. The book received critical acclaim, its revamped version being highlighted as a 2011 University Press Book for Public and Secondary School Libraries and recommended for use in teaching.

properties.Title: Long Beach, NY - Signature Gathering
properties.Description:
Hundreds are expected to attend the annual Martin Luther King Jr. Day Commemorative March in Long Beach on Monday to mark Dr. King’s 91st birthday. The march will honor the life and legacy of Dr. King, the civil-rights leader who was assassinated in 1968. As many already know, Dr. King’s economic dream was a guaranteed income for all Americans.

This year’s keynote speaker will be Dr. Jonathan Shaw, a philanthropist and spiritual leader of the Crown Ministries International, of Brooklyn. Shaw was chosen because of his powerful work helped the lives of many people. Gospel singer Kiy Lewis will be a special guest. Youth vendors from the MLK Center will be on hand.

Help Andrew Yang and our CD NY-4 delegates get on the ballot! We've been given a tall order - to collect a whole bunch of petition signatures (15000 for our Presidential candidate, 1500 for NY-4 delegates) before early February! With a little more help from Yang Gang volunteers, we can hit these goals within the 10 days remaining and keep this campaign rolling.

Whether you plan to volunteer as a signature gatherer or just sign ballot petitions, sign up to come meet some local Yang Gang members, Yang some Long Islanders (super important, because we need more than 15% of votes for a Congressional District to secure DNC delegates), and help Make America Think Harder!

properties.Title: SAN ANTONIO, TEXAS - MARTIN LUTHER KING, JR. MARCH
properties.Venue: Martin Luther King Academy for Arts Integration
properties.Address:
3501 Martin Luther King Dr
San Antonio, TX 78220
properties.Description:
Join us on January 20 for the 33rd Annual Martin Luther King, Jr. March in San Antonio, Texas!! San Antonio is home to the largest MLK March in the Nation and this year the MLK, Jr. Commission is expecting approximately 300,000 participants!
We'll meet at the Martin Luther King Academy for Arts Integration at 3501 Martin Luther King Dr, San Antonio, TX 78220

(This event will be updated and include more event day details as we get closer to the event)

Martin Luther King, Jr. March Activities:

8:45 - 9:10 AM -- Freeman Coliseum Park and Ride to March
10:00 AM -- March in the 30th Annual MLK, Jr. March

We’re excited and proud that Yang Gang will be part of such an incredible event like this year’s MLK March. Many of us have participated in the March before, however this year is different. This year we will get to walk in remembrance of Dr. King, his legacy and the progress he’s inspired while also walking for and representing Andew Yang, the rising Democratic Presidential Candidate and outspoken proponent of Dr. King’s legacy and ideas. This year you can join us in walking and showing support for a Presidential Candidate that is running on the ideas that Martin Luther King, Jr. preached throughout his life, including eradicating poverty, alleviating vast economic disparities in our nation and promoting the importance of the value of each individual as a human and not a number in the economy.

Martin Luther King, Jr. is an American Hero that was a champion in fighting for American Civil Rights and Equality. He’s a great leader in our history that found himself in circumstances where he can make a difference for our country, for millions of his fellow Americans and the generations to come. He ended up dedicating his life to the opportunity of changing the status of his fellow Americans up until the day he was killed while traveling the country promoting the idea of a Universal Basic Income. This base level income would be given to all Americans with the effect of allowing every American a meaningful chance to participate in our capitalist economy.


The obvious equalizing effects of a Universal Basic Income and the need to overcome historic disparities in our great nation has never gone away, and so today we are proud that Presidential Candidate Andrew Yang is courageous enough to run for president on a platform of the Freedom Dividend, calling again as Dr. King did, for a Universal Basic Income for all Americans that will uplift our entire nation, but especially the impoverished, and those historically and currently left behind by our winner-take-all economy. Andrew, who is not a career politician, has also found himself situated in a position where he is able to understand the major problems that are affecting our country and the American people, and he has chosen to act on his position and do something to help. Andrew Yang realizes, similar to Dr. King, that he has the opportunity, and thus the responsibility to take action where he knows that he can make a major difference in the lives of millions of Americans.

We feel that Dr. King would be proud of the fight that Andrew Yang fighting and the direction he wants to take our country.

For these reasons we think it will be a great Honor to Dr. King to March for Andrew Yang with the Yang Gang in this years Martin Luther King, Jr. March in San Antonio.

We really hope you can make it!

Please contact us with any questions or concerns.
Thank you for your time!

properties.Title: Celebrating MLK- Central Jersey Yang Gang Hang
properties.Description:
Secretary of State Tahesha Way and the New Jersey Martin Luther King, Jr. Commemorative Commission invite you to our annual Martin Luther King, Jr. Commemorative event on Sunday, January 19, 2020, from 3:00 to 5:00 p.m. at the NJ State Museum in Trenton.

This year’s program, "Telling Our Story,” will focus on women leaders of the movement for civil rights and equal justice. We will honor young people who have competed in our essay contest about 10 “Women Who Led…..they cared, they dared,” and how their legacy relates to that of Dr. King. We will also focus on the importance of CENSUS 2020, and how the census helps us to tell our story, the story of our families and our communities.

This is a FREE event and is open to the general public. So invite your friends, families, young people, colleagues, neighbors, and those who may be interested in attending an event that reminds us that justice, equality, and peace are attainable. Dr. King said, "We refuse to believe that there are insufficient funds in the great vaults of opportunity in this nation." We look forward to honoring Dr. King with you at this year's commemorative!

properties.Title: Murfreesboro, TN - Canvassing
properties.Description:
It's crunch time, and we need all hands on deck. Here's the time line:

Feb 3: Voter Registration Deadline
Feb 12-25: Early Voting Begins
March 3: Primary Voting (TN is a Super Tuesday state!)

What can we do? The campaign's #1 priority in Tennessee right now is targeted door-to-door canvassing. Real life conversations continue to be one of the most meaningful ways to engage with potential voters. You don't need experience and you don't need to be a policy expert. Just bring your enthusiasm, manners, a mobile device and any literature you would like to distribute.

Let’s meet at Starbucks for a brief training, and fuel up to introduce our neighbors to Andrew Yang!

Volunteers are welcome to join or bow out as needed throughout the day. Keep an eye out for more events as we plan to canvass steadily over the next several weeks. If the schedule doesn't work for you, register anyway so that an organizer can set you up to canvass your area independently or help you team up with another volunteer.

Let's DO this!

properties.Title: MLK Weekend of Service with the Yang Gang - Community lunch for the homeless at Finlay Park
properties.Description:
Every Sunday FNB hosts a Community Picnic in Finlay Park and feeds about 200 of our homeless neighbors. This Sunday we are again helping to serve and then eating together. Please join us and bring your appetite as the food is home-made and delicious.
Needs Include:
*Setup Help. Arrive at 12:45 to help setup tables, fill water cups, wrap forks & napkins and carry food as it's delivered.
*Serving the meal between 1-2, at one of a dozen stations.
*You could donate 8 1/2 inch disposable plates or 8 oz cups or plastic forks.
*Bring food to share. Ideas below. Please make sure that, if applicable, meats are cut into bite sized pieces as there are NO KNIVES at the event. Bring food in disposable (reusable!) covered tin pans OR bring in your own pans/crockpots that you take home after.
The community picnic takes place, rain or shine, under the pavilion at the Taylor Street entrance to Finlay Park.
FNB delivers everything for the setup and coordinates the meat & food donations from local grocers. If you would like to bring a dish to pass, anything is welcome. Sides might include macaroni & cheese, mashed potatoes & gravy, baked beans, any veggies, cookies or anything you feel like making. Other options are pulled pork, baked chicken pieces, meatloaf, cut up sausage, hot dogs, strips of bacon, or anything that can be served on a plate and with a fork. (No soup!) If cooking isn't your best option, please help setup and serve. Call me if you have any questions!

properties.Title: Andrew Yang Town Hall in Waterloo
properties.Description:
Join Andrew for his Town Hall in Waterloo!

Our Town Hall is at the Lark Brewing Company 3295 University Avenue, Waterloo 50701.

Doors open at 11:30. RSVP is not required but encouraged.

---------------
Come meet Andrew Yang! An Entrepreneur. A husband and father. And a non-profit leader.

Andrew Yang will be hosting multiple town halls and events to engage with Iowans and share his bold plans to rewrite the rules of the 21st-century economy so they work fairly for everyone, not just corporations.

Andrew's not a career politician. He's a job creator who understands the economy. That is why as president, Andrew's first priority will be to implement the big solutions America needs to get back on track. To start, he'd enact a $1,000 a month Freedom Dividend, no strings attached, for every American 18 and older. Andrew understands that if the rules of our economy don't work for everyone, they don't work. As the father of two young boys, Andrew is committed to doing everything in his power to create the kind of future our children deserve—one with an America of opportunity, freedom, and equality.

properties.Description:

Shoppers are very receptive. We sell merchandise as well. It is a great opportunity to share information about Yang2020. We provide the materials! Parking is free! Entrance to the mall is free!

properties.Title: Buffalo, NY  - Signature Gathering
properties.Description:
Sunday, January 19th at 12:00PM to 4:00PM

We would like to gather together and collect signatures for the congressional districts to get Andrew Yang on the ballot. Don’t miss this special opportunity to #UNITE – as part of the Weekend of Action! We will meet at Starbucks at 12 o’clock to attend the 1 PM women’s march. See below for more information!

The Women's March of Buffalo/WNY, opposed to all forms of oppression, seeks to increase equity and equality for women and all oppressed people by ensuring structural and systemic changes in our local government, local businesses and organizations, and within society at large in order to guarantee a woman's right to health, safety, and freedom from violence. We seek this regardless of racial, economic, or citizenship status; and value the dignity and humanity of women of color, women with disabilities, and lgbt/queer and gender non-conforming people, and everyone's equal place in the movement and in society.

At Niagara Square, Buffalo NY. Come join in solidarity as we revel in the #womenswave and we #UnitetheStruggles. RSVP here: https://actionnetwork.org/events/womens-march-2020-buffalowny

properties.Title: Honolulu, HI - Crowd-Yanging at Ken Jeong Show
properties.Description: If you haven't already heard, comedian and general physician, Ken Jeong has endorsed Andrew Yang! He'll also be in Honolulu doing two shows on Saturday, January 18th. Bring your swag - we'll have some to share - and get ready to talk to people about why you support Yang. Look for the MATH hats, banners, and other Yang2020 gear.

21 and over only.
https://facebook.com/events/s/yanggang-pub-crawl-ames/202728237529521/?ti=icl

properties.Title: Arcata, CA - Yang Gang Hang
properties.Description:
Thanks for signing up to attend the Humboldt County Yang Gang Hang!

This will be a casual meetup at the Ramones in Wildberries (the sunroom) on every Saturday @ 6:30pm to discuss how to get involved with the campaign and plan for the coming weeks. Specifically will be discussing getting things together for phonebanking parties, fundraisers, and the usual tabling/yanging at local events! The cafe isn't the biggest so will be easy to spot. Look for the redhead with the Yanged out laptop!

Connecting through our Facebook group "Humboldt County Yang Gang" is great, but getting supporters together in-real-life (IRL) is how we can really grow and help Andrew win! The purpose of this meeting is just to get to know other Yang supporters in our community, talk about what drew us to the campaign, and discuss ways to get Andrew to the White House - making calls, sending texts, knocking on doors, but also fun actions at local community events!

This is to be a fairly informal meeting. Don’t feel obligated to prepare anything before hand or feel like you need to have prior campaigning experience to show up. We just want to start building a Yang Gang presence in our community as we approach the Democratic Primary beginning with that early voting in February.

This will hopefully be a great place to prepare for canvassing and brainstorm creative ways to make everyone aware of Yang's message. Bring your ideas, and I will bring Yang Cards to share!

And really this location is just to start, but we can change it if someone thinks up or can offer a more suitable place -and the time as well if another works better for everybody. Can't wait to see everyone there!

properties.Title: Houston, TX - Crowdyanging at Rockets Game against Lakers (Late Shift)
properties.Description:
Yang Gang,

This is the 2nd of 2, two-hour shifts, for Saturday's sports crowdyanging game against the #1 seeded LA Lakers!

Although the game will have started by now, we should still be able to Yang passersby, Toyota Center staff, as well as late arrivals and early leavers. The relative lull will also give us time to prepare for Yanging thousands of either upbeat or disgruntled fans :)

We should still be at La Branch St x Polk St (front entrance of Toyota Center) from the Early Shift, but reach out beforehand in case we have moved.

Bring your best Yang swag and catchiest Yang-lines to MATH the fans with!

properties.Title: NH MATHfest: Music for Andrew Yang featuring  Bigfoot, Ambient Discord

Featuring
Bigfoot

properties.Title: Huntsville, AL - Canvassing Meeting
properties.Description:
Thank you to all that came last weekend! It was a lot of fun and I look forward to seeing familiar faces return this Saturday. Everyone who came said they wanted to volunteer for the campaign and so now for this next meeting I plan to go over the canvassing strategies we'll be using for the Huntsville area. It's a stacked deck against the Yang campaign so we can't afford to be bystanders any longer if we want him to win!

For those of you that haven't made a prior meeting please by all means still come to this! The more help we have in spreading his name recognition the better and you didn't miss anything too important in the last meeting.

Humanity First!

properties.Title: Pizza and Phonebank Saturdays in SF
properties.Description:
It is a TOP CAMPAIGN PRIORITY to call voters in the Early States (Iowa + New Hampshire)!

SFYG is hosting Pizza + Phonebank + Prizes parties every Saturday from 12-4pm.

Drop in at any time between Noon-4pm, whether it's 30 min, an hour, two hours, however much time you can dedicate to get Yang elected!

Just bring your own laptop, earbuds/headphones, and a positive attitude :)

---

January schedule:

- Sat 1/4 @ 425 Market#900, Host: Eric


- Sat 1/11 @ 680 Folsom, Host: Elaine


- Sat 1/18 @ 601 Townsend, Host: Musa (NOTE: Due to SF Women's March, this will be from 4-6pm)

- Sat 1/25 @ 1355 Market#900, Host: Tristan

- Sat 2/1 @ USF, Host: Ethan

Things to note:
- You won't be using your personal phone number, the Yang Dialer will automatically dial for you
- If it's your first time, we'll get you trained and up and running!
- If 5+ sign up, we'll order pizza!
- We'll also have PRIZES for callers who have the most conversations - gift cards/merch! :)

Optional:
- See the docs below to prep!
- If you can't make it to our parties, it's easy to make calls on your own time:

Training video: https://www.loom.com/share/32a5238ab95d41559632158f514e7774

Preview script: https://desktop.thrutalk.io/candidate/yang-iowa-voter-id

properties.Title: Houston, TX - Crowdyanging at Rockets Game against Lakers (Early Shift)
properties.Description:
Yang Gang,

This is the 1st of 2, two-hour shifts, for Saturday's sports crowdyanging game against the #1 seeded LA Lakers!

Rockets fans start trickling in 1.5 hours prior to the game before it becomes a flood, and then trickles back down 30 minutes after the game starts. We will therefore arrive 1.5 hours early to set up our canvasses and catch both trickles and the flood.

We will meet outside the at La Branch St x Clay St with the outdoor basketball courts as a landmark, and then move as a group towards La Branch St x Polk St.

Bring your best Yang swag and catchiest Yang-lines to MATH the fans with!

properties.Title: Andrew Yang Town Hall in Buchanan County!
properties.Description:
Join Andrew for his Town Hall in Buchanan County!

Our Town Hall is at the Buchanan County Fairgrounds 4H Building.

Cash bar. Doors open at 5:30pm. RSVP is not required but encouraged.

---------------
Come meet Andrew Yang! An Entrepreneur. A husband and father. And a non-profit leader.

Andrew Yang will be hosting multiple town halls and events to engage with Iowans and share his bold plans to rewrite the rules of the 21st-century economy so they work fairly for everyone, not just corporations.

Andrew's not a career politician. He's a job creator who understands the economy. That is why as president, Andrew's first priority will be to implement the big solutions America needs to get back on track. To start, he'd enact a $1,000 a month Freedom Dividend, no strings attached, for every American 18 and older. Andrew understands that if the rules of our economy don't work for everyone, they don't work. As the father of two young boys, Andrew is committed to doing everything in his power to create the kind of future our children deserve—one with an America of opportunity, freedom, and equality.

properties.Title: Weekend Phone Bank: West Des Moines
properties.Address:
950 Office Park Rd 125
West Des Moines, IA 50265
properties.Description:
With only a handful of weeks remaining before the Caucus, join the Yang Gang as we continue to build our wave of momentum before it crashes down on Feb. 3 the business as usual system stacked against working class Iowans.

We have the grassroots energy to win this election, but we can’t let up if we want to rewrite the rules of the 21st century and put Andrew Yang in the White House. So let’s knock on every door and make every phone call we can to show our friends and neighbors how a Humanity First national would benefit them.

Every day our passionate supporters reach out to those in their communities to share Andrew’s plans to create opportunity for every American and ensure our children the future they deserve.

If you’ve never volunteered before, no worries! Our friendly staff will help catch you up to speed. In fact, many of Andrew Yang’s most ardent volunteers are first time Caucus goers. What matters most is that you realize your own power. In every door knock and every phone call, our movement is one step closer to achieving Andrew’s vision: an America of opportunity, freedom, and equality, for every person.

Please join us and be a part of that effort. Nothing short of the future of our nation is at stake.

Note: If you do, thank you! Please bring a fully charged cell phone. We've got everything else you will need, including Andrew Yang merchandise for volunteers that help multiple times!

This event’s address is private. Sign up for more details
Los Angeles, CA 90015
properties.Description:
Thanks for signing up to attend this Text Banking Event! Yang Gang does not have enough volunteers in Iowa, so we must volunteer digitally to connect with voters. Iowa is an essential state that we must outreach. Our concentration will be rural Iowa.

Below is what we plan to do:
* Immediately send Voter Identification texts to thousands of potential voters
* Get trained to text if you haven’t already gone through the training process.
* If you can, follow this step-by-step guide to get trained prior to the event: http://bit.ly/35Qhi9Q

Note:
Sorry, this space is NOT "child" friendly. No one will be admitted under the age of 17! No exceptions.

This is a private business that is offering office space for Yang Gang text banking. The max capacity is 12 people at a time. You do not have to stay for the full hours of this event, but the minimum hours of volunteering that's expected is 2.

Feel free to bring a potluck of food and drinks to share. There are also local restaurants on the ground floor of this building.

properties.Title: Phone Bank for New Hampshire
properties.Description:
HIGH PRIORITY: New Hampshire primary is February 11th! These calls will be focused on identifying voters.

Please Note: We are using votebuilder and manually dialing phone numbers (NOT the dialer).

3 Easy Steps:

1) RSVP to see training video link.
2) Send me your slack username to be added to a private NH callers channel *OR* I can email you a call list link.
3) Create an Action ID or log in to start making calls.

Weekdays: 3 PM - 8PM EST
Weekends: 10 AM - 8 PM EST

On Saturdays we hold a zoom call for 30 minutes at 2:30 PM EST with all attendees, link: https://zoom.us/j/860503073

On weekdays, I am available for 1:1 Q&A support.

properties.Title: 📞 Call for Yang! ☎️
properties.Description:
### [Call for Yang TODAY!](https://www.yang2020.com/call/)

Hey Yang Gang! Calling early state voters is one of the most impactful thing we can be doing right now to help Andrew get elected. We truly can't thank you all enough for your support and commitment to this movement.

Follow the steps below to get started:

1. Join our Yang 2020 Slack where you can chat with other callers and ask questions by [opening this link in a separate tab](https://www.yang2020.com/join-volunteer-slack/).

2. Everything you need to know about making calls can be found in our Call Team Handbook which you can check out by [opening this link in a separate tab](https://docs.google.com/document/d/17xNaWzkv6ZxpU2dQECmDFc8KcTuNj_ZOAXf9yy8jrJM/edit?usp=sharing)

3. Sign up for as many shifts as you'd like by filling in your info on the right side of your screen! If something changes with your schedule, don't worry about cancelling. The dialer is usually open from 11:00AM CT to 8:00PM CT. Occasionally, it is open for longer, give or take an hour or two. We're *strongly* encouraging everyone to sign up at "peak hours" 3:00PM CT - 7:00PM CT in order to minimize the wait time between calls.

4. Once in the Yang 2020 Slack, go to the #callers_start_here channel where Calling Support will be able to answer any questions you have!

Roxana L Rivera

ALL IN THE BRONX

properties.Title: Tampa, FL - Yang Gang  At The Black Heritage Festival
properties.Description:
The Tampa Bay Yang Gang is proud to announce we will be participating at the Black Heritage Festival in Tampa January 18th and 19th.

Volunteers are needed for many shifts throughout the weekend.

The event will begin at 7:30am till 10:30am on Saturday for a walk/run beginning at Curtis Hixon Park. This will be prime opportunity to Yang and cheer on runners and walkers.

Set-up on Saturday can begin at 7am and must finish by 11am. The festival begins at 12pm and will run until 9pm.

Set-up on Sunday will be 12pm with the festival starting at 1pm, and running till 9pm.

We will have a booth under a shared tent with a table and 2 chairs, and need a minimum of 2 volunteers for each shift. Extra volunteers can stand or walk the festival.

Please sign-up for a shift on this sign-up sheet. If you have any trouble or additional questions please email: TampaBayYangGang@mail.com

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1xPZ9gmfm_k5BMDQhtywigHeV-K7xKtJDuQqEbZjZMNg/edit?usp=drivesdk

properties.Title: Become an Event Moderator
properties.Description:
Yang2020 event postings are coming in at increasing speeds. It's a great problem to have, but the Yang2020 event support team is going to need your help if we want to keep up!

We're looking for volunteer moderators to edit and approve events. We're also looking for volunteer callers to contact new event hosts and prepare them for their events. If either or both of these tasks sound interesting to you, then signup and begin the on-boarding process today!
